The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Aug. 20: Air-India will allow passengers to carry a small cabin baggage on UK-bound flights. 

 An official said mobile phones, laptops and gadgets such as iPods will also be allowed.

 Calcutta: Dacoits stabbed to death Kanai Sardar, a 55-year-old railway employee, in his house at Taldi in Canning on Saturday night after he raised an alarm. The goons were on their way out when the alarm was raised. They returned and killed Sardar in front of his wife and son. After they left, neighbours rushed to the house. Police said the goons took away Rs 15,000 and other valuables. 

 Bolpur: The decks have been cleared for the recruitment of women firefighters, fire services minister Pratim Chatterjee said here. The government will soon start recruiting women, he added. In the first lot, about 35 of them would be trained.

 Calcutta: Two youths were found dead near a railway cabin at Kankurgachhi, between Bidhannagar and Sealdah stations, on Sunday morning. Railway police said the boys, aged around 20, were hit by a train. 

 A man in his forties was crushed by a train while trying to cross the tracks at Sodepur in North 24-Parganas in the evening. None of the dead has been identified.




